      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Looks a good race. LAWS WARS (3) stepped up to this journey at third run for the new yard and broke through for a maiden win. Drops in weight after the claim and can go close again. STANDARD STREET (4) resumed over 1000m and was beaten a head by GRINZINGER TUNDRA in an eye-catching return. Fitter and extra trip looks ideal. Meets the winner slightly better at the weights and can turn the tables. GRINZINGER TUNDRA (2) was immediately off the mark for the new yard with a determined win. The former Victorian does look well placed here at the longer trip though and can go close again. PRICE SHARE (5) made debut in that same race and placed third. Can only be improved and likely to be highly competitive again. LEVERAGED BUYOUT (1) is in form and will give a sight again.",
